The paper deals with designing a time-domain equalizer for PAM-based optical interconnects, which involves signal processing and communication theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence algorithms, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of parallel processing could also fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
